  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Woe to Oppressors"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who devise iniquity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and plot evil on their beds!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "At morning’s light they accomplish it",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because the power is in their hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They covet fields and seize them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they take away houses.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They deprive a man of his home,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a fellow man of his inheritance.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Therefore this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am planning against this nation a disaster",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from which you cannot free your necks.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then you will not walk so proudly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for it will be a time of calamity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day they will take up a proverb against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and taunt you with this bitter lamentation:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "‘We are utterly ruined!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has changed the portion of my people.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "How He has removed it from me!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has allotted our fields to traitors.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, you will have no one in the assembly of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to divide the land by lot.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Reproof of False Prophets"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Do not preach,” they preach.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Do not preach these things;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "disgrace will not overtake us.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Should it be said, O house of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Is the Spirit of the LORD impatient?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Are these the things He does?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not My words bring good",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to him who walks uprightly?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But of late My people have risen up",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an enemy:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You strip off the splendid robe",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from unsuspecting passersby",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like men returning from battle.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You drive the women of My people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from their pleasant homes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You take away My blessing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from their children forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Arise and depart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for this is not your place of rest,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because its defilement brings destruction—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a grievous destruction!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If a man of wind were to come",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and say falsely,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will preach to you of wine and strong drink,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3818
          },
          {
            "text": "he would be just the preacher for this people!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Remnant of Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will surely gather all of you, O Jacob;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will collect the remnant of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bring them together like sheep in a pen,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a flock in the midst of its pasture—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a noisy throng.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One who breaks open the way",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will go up before them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will break through the gate,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and go out by it.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their King will pass through before them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD as their leader.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3818,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or “I will prophesy to you for wine and strong drink”",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 2,
          "verse": 11
        }
      }
    ]
